			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>June 3rd 1856 5616</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
				<p>Below I beg to hand you lists of officers<lb/> elected to serve the <sic>ensueing</sic> year of<lb/> our Ladies &#38; Gentlemens Hebrew<lb/> Benevolent associations</p>
				<list type="simple">
				<head>Ladies Hebrew Ben Society</head>
				<item>x <persName>Mrs A Haber</persName>  President</item>
				<item>   <persName>Mrs C Hyams</persName>  vice President</item>
				<item>x <persName>Mrs L Goldsmith</persName>  Treasurer</item>
				<item>x <persName>Mrs M Goldsmith</persName>  Secretary</item>
				<item>x <persName>Mrs A Block</persName></item>
				<item>x <persName>Mrs I L Levy</persName></item>
				<item>x <persName>Mrs A Marxs</persName></item>
				<item>x <persName>Mrs A Adler</persName></item>
				<item>x <persName>Mrs Ed. Jacobs</persName></item>
				</list>
				<p>x re elected</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<list type="simple">
				<head>Gentlemens Hebrew Benevolent association</head>
				<item>x <persName>Jos Simon</persName>  President</item>
				<item>  <persName>Jos Cohn</persName>  vice Do</item>
				<item>x <persName>R Block</persName>  Treasurer</item>
				<item>x <persName>Jos Rosenfeld</persName>  Secretary</item>
				<item>x <persName>S Forcheimer</persName>  Trustees</item>
				<item>x <persName>L Mayer</persName></item>
				<item>   <persName>A Levi</persName></item>
				<item>x <persName>J C Labatt</persName></item>
				</list>
				<p>x re elected</p>
				<p>I have the honor to be chairman of the Committee<lb/> on &#8220;application &#38; relief&#8221; of our widows &#38; orphans<lb/> Home &#38; can assure you scarcely a week has<lb/> passed since the opening of our Building but<lb/> I have been called upon to grant admission<lb/> for some poor widow or orphans the rooms<lb/> are <sic>rappidly</sic> filling up &#38; under the able management<lb/> of <persName>Mrs Depass</persName> the Institution is a pleasure to visit<lb/> which I am happy to inform you is the daily resort<lb/> of many of our families.  A school has been<lb/> <sic>opend</sic> in the building a long number of<lb/> school Books &#38; other stationary provided<lb/> which is under the charge of <persName>Miss Emanuel</persName></p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>none visit the Building but leave it with<lb/> feelings of pride that such a Building &#38;<lb/> Its able management is devoted to the<lb/> unfortunate.  I shall rejoice if ever you<lb/> favour our city with a visit to have you<lb/> go through the Buildings grounds Gardens &#38;c<lb/> of the Home for Jewish widows &#38; orphans</p>
				<p>In a few Days I shall report all Collections<lb/> with Draft for same</p>
			<p>until then <hi rend="indent(1)">I am ever faithfully yours</hi></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName></p>
				<p>The new Synagogue on <placeName>Carondelet Street</placeName><lb/> is progressing instruction I do not <sic>beleive</sic><lb/> it can be <sic>finishd</sic> earlier than <date>February</date> next<lb/> I believe it is the Intention of <persName>Mr G<lb/> Kursheedt</persName> &#38; <persName>Rev J K Gutheim</persName> to<lb/> visit your northern cities this Summer</p>
				<p><persName>Mrs Hart</persName> &#38; family &#38; your numerous<lb/> friends join in kind regards</p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
				<p>I would avail myself of this<lb/> to name some that has paid for<lb/> the Occident lately I may have<lb/> named some before but when<lb/> I report it may come too late for the<lb/> <date>July</date> number so I mention them now</p>
